  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mozambique Transparency and Accountability for Inclusive Development (TAcID) is a three and a half year programme funded by the U.K. Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office. TAcID works with local actors &#x2013; civil society organizations, government ministries and local government authorities, and the donor community &#x2013; to support national reforms to improve governance transparency, accountability, and responsiveness to civic demands by pushing for more responsible resource management and inclusive, participatory planning and decision-making processes.</narrative>
  </description>
